│ vectorizer is due to an attempt to create an invalid cast instruction. This happens        │
│ because the vectorizer's code generation logic for casts does not correctly handle cases   │
│ where the scheduler has reordered the scalar instructions within a bundle. It incorrectly  │
│ assumes the type of the first scalar instruction (`TE.Scalars[0]`) is representative for   │
│ all lanes, which leads to a type mismatch when creating the vectorized cast.               │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will modify the `BoUpSLP::vectorizeTree` function in                        │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`. Specifically, when handling cast        │
│ instructions, I will ensure that the destination type for the vectorized cast is           │
│ determined by the type of the scalar instruction in the *current lane* being processed,    │
│ rather than always using the first one.                                                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ This change will make the vectorization of casts robust to instruction reordering by the   │
│ scheduler.                                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
